<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5>direct something at someone • direct something to someone</xh5><p> <i>direct something at someone—</i>1. aim or point smth. at a person: Wary troopers <u>directed stun guns at</u> the medley of bodies in case of disorder. 2. intend smth. for a person: Are you <u>directing your remarks at</u> me?</p><p> <i>direct something to someone—</i>1. address or send smth. to a person: Please <u>direct all the mail to</u> the secretary when it is delivered. 2. <i>= direct something at someone 2: </i>My next remarks are <u>directed to</u> the boys and girls of this school.</p> </entry>
